<div id="review_61877302" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/61877302" />
    <a title="MaryKay" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1041061-marykay"><img alt="MaryKay" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1285901745p2/1041061.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/61877302?book_show_action=true">Jul 02, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="MaryKay" class="user" itemprop="url" name="MaryKay" href="/user/show/1041061-marykay">MaryKay</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1041061-marykay?shelf=2009">2009</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer61877302" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10813325091841829961">The characters in this book have faults. Their lives are not what they would have planned or chosen. But repentance and forgiveness happen. In chapter 16, I liked where it said, &quot;He was pruning the olive trees in the wrong season. His watering was washing away too much topsoil around the vines. But he didn&apos;t care. He would do better tomorrow.&quot; Some days we aren&apos;t able to do things perfectly, but we do the best we can.</span>
  <span id="freeText10813325091841829961" style="display:none">The characters in this book have faults. Their lives are not what they would have planned or chosen. But repentance and forgiveness happen. In chapter 16, I liked where it said, "He was pruning the olive trees in the wrong season. His watering was washing away too much topsoil around the vines. But he didn't care. He would do better tomorrow." Some days we aren't able to do things perfectly, but we do the best we can.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10813325091841829961" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
