<span id="freeTextContainer18285917446333853568">Ah, that all books could be this good. I do think you need to be 30 and over to truly enjoy the book. Meaning, you have to have lived life long enough to get the pain and anguish of regret and disappointment and the joy of forgiveness to appreciate the characters. Otherwise, this book would just come across as a fun, delightful read. </span>

          </span>
